node.text: This is truly heartbreaking, I saw this post on @askfly1 page and it brought tears to my eyes. This is tragic. Looking at these graves, my heart cries for all the loved ones that’s dealing with the hurt from losing them. So many of our young men & women are losing their lives at alarming rates due to violence in our city.

Life is one great big adventure, we’re all still learning, we all have our ups and downs and we all have our struggles. We're much more alike than we are different....so let’s use our stories and platforms to empower one another oppose to putting each other down. Let’s spread love, knowledge, unity and peace. 
Ps: anyone can join the Womanaire Club just click the follow button and you’re in the club @womanaireclub 

Happy women’s month 🏆

node.text:
If you feel like learning something important today watch this and then share it, and never stop sharing it. Let’s continue to educate ourselves on Black History, start having these conversations at the dinner table with your family, partner and friends. And ask yourself what else don’t we know? And how can we change the narrative. For starters they need to get rid of those deceptive ass history textbooks and start telling our true history.
Ps: if you know anyone that has written any books on this please share I’d love to add it to my library. 

Happy Black History Month🖤🏆🙌🏽

node.text:
This is the process of making Milano denim. From concept, sketch, design, raw cotton, weaving, dyeing, tacking, washing, distressing, embroidering, etc. thought, love, quality and care went into every pair of denim we make. Let’s normalize black owned luxury!! It’s black history month, celebrate the fact that we have black owned denim instead of bashing about prices. 
I searched, source & sampled the finest denim. Our men’s, unisex & babies denim is imported from Milan, Italy. Our halo and Harlow denim is imported from Turkey, the first sample we made was from Milan, Italy but the stretch just wasn’t hugging the curves the way I envisioned women’s denim to hug every curve and accentuate our waistline so I went with the finest denim from turkey. Please don’t undermine Black owned luxury. Get use to it, because it’s plenty more black designers on the rise and soon this will be the norm!!
Ps: thank you all for supporting @milanodirouge 
#milanodirouge #blackluxury

NOT TO MENTION WHILE I WAS OUT IN MILAN, ITALY VISITING THE DENIM FACTORY, WALKING AROUND THEIR MASSIVE WAREHOUSE I STARTED FEELING THE PAIN OF MY KIDNEY STONES AND I JUST KEPT WORKING BECAUSE I NEEDED TO LEARN THE PROCESS AND TEST THE DENIM AS WELL AS SEE THEIR WORKING CONDITIONS BUT I WENT ON BED REST FOR THE NEXT 2 DAYS WHILE IN MILAN BECAUSE THEM STONES WAS KICKING MY ASS. I HAD TO CALL A DOCTOR TO COME TO MY HOTEL ROOM AND TREAT ME. SO DON’T QUESTION MY PRICES, RESPECT MY HUSTLE. Please & thanks!!

.
.

node.text:
Forgive my language, but let me show you a badass motherfucker. ⁣
⁣
When Larry Krasner became the District Attorney of Philadelphia in 2017, one of his first acts was coming in to fire the prosecutors from his office who lied on and cheated and framed innocent people. ⁣
⁣
30 of them. Gone in one quick swoop. ⁣
⁣
These corrupt men and women protected dirty cops and caused innocent people to lose a combined hundreds of years of their lives in prison. ⁣
⁣
Do you know how much guts this took?⁣
⁣
This is the type of change we talk about, but very few people actually deliver on. ⁣
⁣
LARRY DELIVERED! ⁣
⁣
And now he needs us to have his back. Because every corrupt cop and prosecutor in Philly and in all of Pennsylvania is coming for him - not only threatening to kill him, but now trying to defeat him with one of these very corrupt prosecutors who got fired for protecting him. ⁣
⁣
I say HELL NO. ⁣
⁣
And I need you to say HELL NO. ⁣
⁣
Please, please, please CLICK THE LINK IN MY BIO and donate whatever you can to help re-elect Larry Krasner. ⁣
⁣
He's my hero - and is the hero to many of us across the country doing this work. ⁣
⁣
Police are going to spend millions to defeat him. ⁣
⁣
And we can't let that happen. Give whatever you can - $5, $25, $100, or more if you have it. ⁣
⁣
Give monthly if you can. He needs it. ⁣
⁣
And tell everybody you know about him and share the link in my bio so that they can give too, OK?⁣
⁣
Let's GO! ⁣
⁣
Let me know below when you've chipped in. ⁣
⁣
Love y’all. ⁣
⁣
—Shaun

node.title: Watch this clip, especially if you’re from Philly!! R/p @shaunking

node.text:
This was an amazing movie. I feel like everyone need to watch this. Black ppl, brown ppl, white ppl, police officers, government officials, lawmakers, and anyone raising black or brown sons. 
 It was so well written, so well played and thought out, it helps you to understand the pain, anguish and process of a parent grieving, and it helps you to understand the laws, and how our rights as civilians don’t apply to us but it should!!! I learned a lot watching this movie. I’m watching it again with my family tonight. I want us to have a discussion about it. #americanskin 
SHARE THIS MOVIE ON YOUR PAGE OR YOUR STORY. Let’s get the message out. A lot of times when black ppl make movies with powerful messages it gets shadow banned because they don’t like for our stories to be told by us. They rather tell it so they can paint a certain picture. So watch it & let me know your thoughts

node.text:
You see the house I pointed to on Reno st, that’s the house I grew up in. I lived there from 8 to 14yrs old. I’ve seen so much happen on my block, I remember when I was 11 sitting on my neighbors porch I watched as my dad pulled up in his green Lexus I assumed he was going to stop when he saw me but he sped pass me (i was disappointed cuz i we locked eyes so I know he saw me) & pulled over in the middle of my block and hopped out the car and ran down an alley way I then noticed that the back window of his car was completely shot out because someone was shooting at him. I’ve seen so much bad shit growing up that I really thought it was normal. I could tell y’all traumatic stories for days but man when I just think about how God saved me and my family and blessed me with an amazing mother that instilled faith in Christ in me... All I can do praise him. 
I praise him not only for blessing me with a business that changed my life i also praise him for helping me change my mindset. I wasn’t always this positive person. Growing up In the hood around a bunch of negative shit will turn you into cold-person. I’ve been in so many fights, drama, and just a bunch of bullshit and just thinking of who I was and looking at the woman I’ve become I give all credit and praises to God. When ppl ask me what’s my secret I always say Him. Idk what my life would be like without Jesus Christ he gets me through everything.
Ps: I started Milano Di Rouge with 2 shirts I wore one and sold the other. I’ve sold my shirts out the trunk of my girl for 2yrs until I got my warehouse in 2014. 
Im just a Philly girl from the hood who believed in her dream, if I can do it anyone can do it. Only thing stopping you is you.

I’m having a class on December 10th sharing tips on how to build your business. If you’re interested in attending. The link for tickets is in @womanaireclub bio

node.text:
Keys open doors 🏆
Yesterday I closed on 3 Mixed-use commercial properties.
What do y’all think I’m going to do with them? 
.

Im from Da Bottom (west Philly) statistics show that I’m not suppose to be to successful. But fck statistics!! We’re changing the narrative. The bottom may be where you start but it doesn’t have to be where you stay. My upbringing made me a hustler. I’ve been surrounded by hustlers my whole life. It’s just most of them hustled illegally and ended up dead or in jail. No one really taught / showed us legal hustles. Since 2012 when I started @milanodirouge I have used my platform to show the struggles and the beauty of running a business and building a brand. I didn’t want to just show the glamorous part of entrepreneurship because I wanted y’all to know that it’s not as glamorous  as it may look. This shit is hard!! I wanted y’all to be inspired by how I overcame the odds so you can know that you can overcome them too.
And I wanted y’all to be inspired by how I didn’t give up no matter how hard this journey got for me. Last year, when i had my son, I started thinking about my legacy and what i will pass on to him. I realized i had lots of success and material things but no real ownership. So I made a decision to start investing in real estate. 
I got my first investment property (a Mixed-use commercial building) I purchased my house and i got my mom and sis an investment property. This year I got a few more investment properties. I haven’t shared much of this part of my journey because I’m so use to sharing the struggle with y’all and I didn’t want to feel as if I was boasting my blessings. But I made up my mind that I’ll continue to share both because sometimes all it takes is for a person to see it to know that it’s attainable and to know that they can do it too. I come from the hood, believe me when I say, If I can do it, you can do it too. You just have to believe you can. 

@MilanoDiRouge means Making Dreams Reality. My goal is to inspire our customers, supporters & followers to MAKE their DREAMS a REALITY!

Keychain @milanodirouge
